DOCREF="LA081489-0025"
SELECTOR="K"
SUMMARIZER="G">  

The wreckage of a plane that crashed against a mountain in Ethiopia
Sunday with Texas Congressman Mickey Leland and 15 others aboard has
been located by US rescue and recovery teams.  Leland, Chairman of the
House Select Committee on Hunger, was making his sixth tour of refugee
camps.  He was accompanied by congressional staff members and
officials of the State Department, Agency for International
Development, and the Ethiopian government.  Indications are that the
passengers and crew died instantly.  President Bush and House Speaker
Thomas Foley highly praised Leland for his sense of compassion and
desire to help those in need.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d59"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="LA081589-0043"
SELECTOR="K"
SUMMARIZER="G">  

Congressman Larkin Smith (D-Miss) died in a light plane crash in
Mississippi Sunday.  Smith was the second House member to die in an
aviation accident this week.  Representative Mickey Leland (D-Tex) and
15 others were found dead Sunday after their plane crashed on an
Ethiopian mountainside.  Smith was a police chief and then a county
sheriff coordinating anti-drug efforts of federal, local, and state
agencies across five states.  Last November, he was elected to
represent Mississippi's 5th Congressional District, replacing Senator
Trent Lott (R-Miss).  He was developing a reputation on the House
Judiciary Committee as a zealous opponent of illegal drugs.</SUM>

<SUM
